      • getAuthenticationToken

        protected AuthenticationToken getAuthenticationToken()
        This utility method gets an authenticated CliAuthenticationToken from the authentication service. Worth noting in this method is that the password is not sent as a credential, because this would imply sending it (or its hash) in cleartext over the network. Instead, it's only sent as part of a SHA1 hash (as part of the CliAuthenticationToken specification). Actual check of the password's validity will formally occur at the first time that the authentication token is checked for authorization. Note also that the CliAuthenticationToken may only be used for a single call via remote. I.e once it's passed through the network once, it's invalid for further use.
        Returns:
        a single use CliAuthenticationToken.
